definition.value: The keto tautomer of cyanuric acid.
An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of pyruvate dehydrogenase (acetyl-transferring) kinase (EC 2.7.11.2).
A 1,3,5-triphenylcyclohexane in which two phenyl groups are on the same side of the cyclohexane ring and the third phenyl group is on the opposite side.
A 1,3,5-triphenylcyclohexane in which all three phenyl groups are on the same side of the cyclohexane ring.
A group that is derived from 7,8-dihydro-8-oxoguanine.

A branched heptasaccharide derivative consisting of a backbone of four alpha-D-mannose residues linked sequentially (1->3), with the residues at the non-reducing end and at the one proximal to the residue at the reducing end acetylated at O-6, and with a beta-D-glucuronosyl residue and two beta-D-xylosyl residues linked (1->2) to the main chain as shown in the diagram. One of a number of synthetic oligosaccharides used to create a synthetic strategy to Cryptococcus neoformans glucuronoxylomannan (GXM) capsular polysaccharide part structures.
An N-acylserotonin resulting from the formal condensation of the primary amino group of serotonin with the carboxy group of acetic acid.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of piroheptine, arising from the protonation of the pyrrolidine nitrogen. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A branched decasaccharide derivative consisting of a backbone of five alpha-D-mannose residues linked sequentially (1->3), with the middle residue carrying a beta-D-glucuronosyl residue via a (1->2) linkage. All of the remaining four mannose residues carry beta-D-xylosyl residues also linked (1->2), while three of the chain of five mannose residues are also acetylated at O-6 as depicted in the diagram. One of a number of synthetic oligosaccharides used to create a synthetic strategy to Cryptococcus neoformans glucuronoxylomannan (GXM) capsular polysaccharide part structures.
A dicarboxylic acid anion that is conjugate base of dainic acid A, arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy groups and protonation of the pyrrolidine nitrogen. Major species at pH 7.3.
A ruthenium coordination entity that is the sodium salt of tetrachloro[bis(1H-indazole)]ruthenate(III). It is a anticancer drug in clinical development for the treatment of solid tumours.

A member of the class of indoles that is (betaS)-beta-methyl-D-tryptophan in which the primary amino group undergoes formal condensation with the carboxy group of 4-(2-oxo-2,3-dihydro-1H-benzimidazol-1-yl)piperidine-1-carboxylic acid and the carboxy group undegoes formal condensation with the amino group of (1R,3S)-cyclohexane-1,3-diyldimethanamine. It is a selective nonpeptidic agonist of the somatostatin subtype-2 (SST2) receptor with Ki of 0.05 nM.
An organochlorine compound that is dichloro-substituted acetamide containing a nitrobenzene ring, an amide bond and two alcohol functions.
A dialkyl ketone with methyl and nonyl as the two alkyl groups.
